wikipedia_page.main: James Ferd Olney (1 August 1914 – 14 September 1944), sometimes written as James Fred Olney, was an English professional footballer who played in the Football League for Birmingham and Swindon Town. He was killed on active service with the Coldstream Guards during the Second World War.

link_mentions.page: List of footballers killed during World War II
response: * Jim Olney – played for Birmingham (1936–1938) and Swindon Town (1938–44). Killed in Belgium on 14 September 1944 aged 30 while serving as lance sergeant in the Coldstream Guards.
